b"[![](../../cdshop/cdinfo.jpg)](../../cdshop/index.htm)  \n[Sacred Texts](../../index.htm)  [Hinduism](../index.htm)  [Index](index.htm)\n[Previous](sbe07014.htm)  [Next](sbe07016.htm)\n\n* * *\n\np. 60\n\n# XIII.\n\nNow follows the (rule regarding the ordeal by) poison.\n\n2\\. All (other) sorts of poison must be avoided (in administering this\nordeal),\n\n3\\. Except poison from the _Sri_ _n_ ga tree, which grows on the Himalayas.\n\n4\\. (Of that) the judge must give seven grains, mixed with clarified butter,\nto the defendant (while reciting the prayer hereafter mentioned).\n\n5\\. If the poison is digested easily, without violent symptoms, he shall\nrecognise him as innocent, and dismiss him at the end of the day.\n\n6\\. 'On account of thy venomous and dangerous nature thou art destruction to\nall living creatures; thou, O poison, knowest what mortals, do not comprehend.\n\n7\\. 'This man being arraigned in a cause, desires to be cleared from guilt.\nTherefore mayest thou deliver him lawfully from this perplexity.'\n\n* * *\n\n[Next: XIV.](sbe07016.htm)\n\n"